The cause of the fire is unclear and no property is at risk at this stage but 70 firefighters have bee dispatched to suppress it. CAPE TOWN - A fire has broken out on Table Mountain. The cause of the fire is unclear and no property is at risk at this stage. Working on Fire's Lauren Howard said: “Three helicopters and a spotter plane form Working on Fire and 70 firefighters have been dispatched to assist Table Mountain National Park, PDMC and the City of Cape Town in suppressing a fire that broke out above Tafelberg Road.”  